  "text": "If the household illegally disposes of waste, then the cost per unit of waste to the household is δ and the per unit environmental cost is so that per unit total social cost of illegal waste is δ + If the household legally disposes of waste, then the regulator bears the cost per unit of waste equal to γ (e.g., collecting and sorting wastes, incineration, operating landfills, and the social and environmental cost of legal disposal). Unless the household is directly charged for legal waste disposal, it is assumed to be a costless activity to undertake. [CITATION_1] It is assumed that the cost to the regulator of legal waste disposal is higher than the private cost of illegal waste disposal but lower than the social cost of illegal waste disposal, δ < γ < δ + . This assumption seems not only reasonable but also makes the whole issue of regulated waste management nontrivial.",
